uld violate that. So, should I remove the placeholder and create a new UtilTest.kt?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying UtilTest implementation**\\n\\nI’m organizing the `UtilTest` class, which is public by default and needs imports. I'll place it in `src/test/kotlin/com/squareup/moshi/moshi/UtilTest.kt`. There might not need to be direct reflection; using `com.squareup.moshi.internal.Util.lookupDefaultsConstructor` is acceptable. We have to keep tests outside library packages. \\n\\nFor Kotlin's generated bytecode with the array constructor and JsonAdapter methods, I'll ensure I handle nullable values carefully. I also need to consider naming the test class properly and generating appropriate tests as I go.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Deciding on UtilTest naming**\\n\\nI think the name `UtilTest.kt` might be a bit ambiguous, but it seems okay since top-level classes in Kotlin are public by default. Maintaining clarity in naming is important, though. I want to ensure it accurately reflects what the file contains and its purpose. Perhaps I could improve the naming for better understanding but for now, it seems functional. I'll keep that in mind if I decide to revisit it later.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_nuTTgPN1U9owiwFOhRpUTowp|fc_093a46819803f25c0169f9807779d0819d962686652ed1b82f", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.squareup.moshi/moshi/1.15.2/src/test/kotlin/com_squareup_moshi/moshi/UtilTest.kt", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage com_squareup_moshi.moshi\n\nimport com.squareup.moshi.JsonAdapter\nimport com.squareup.moshi.JsonClass\nimport com.squareup.moshi.JsonReader\nimport com.squareup.moshi.JsonWriter\nimport com.squareup.moshi.Moshi\nimport com.squareup.moshi.Types\nimport com.squareup.moshi.internal.Util\nimport java.lang.reflect.Type\nimport org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\n\npublic class UtilTest {\n    @Test\n    fun generatedAdapterUsesMoshiConstructorForPlainType(): Unit {\n        val moshi: Moshi = Moshi.Builder().build()\n        val adapter: JsonAdapter<PlainWithMoshi> = moshi.adapter(PlainWithMoshi::class.java)\n\n        assertThat(adapter.toJson(PlainWithMoshi(\"unused\"))).isEqualTo(\"\\\"plain-moshi\\\"\")\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    fun generatedAdapterFallsBackToNoArgumentConstructorForPlainType(): Unit {\n        val moshi: Moshi = Moshi.Builder().build()\n        val adapter: JsonAdapter<PlainWithoutMoshi> = moshi.adapter(PlainWithoutMoshi::class.java)\n\n        assertThat(adapter.toJson(PlainWithoutMoshi(\"unused\"))).isEqualTo(\"\\\"plain-no-args\\\"\")\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    fun generatedAdapterUsesMoshiAndTypeArrayConstructorForParameterizedType(): Unit {\n        val moshi: Moshi = Moshi.Builder().build()\n        val type: Type = Types.newParameterizedType(BoxWithMoshi::class.java, String::class.java)\n        val adapter: JsonAdapter<BoxWithMoshi<String>> = moshi.adapter(type)\n\n        assertThat(adapter.toJson(BoxWithMoshi(\"unused\"))).isEqualTo(\"\\\"box-moshi-java.lang.String\\\"\")\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    fun generatedAdapterFallsBackToTypeArrayConstructorForParameterizedType(): Unit {\n        val moshi: Moshi = Moshi.Builder().build()\n        val type: Type = Types.newParameterizedType(BoxWithoutMoshi::class.java, String::class.java)\n        val adapter: JsonAdapter<BoxWithoutMoshi<String>> = moshi.adapter(type)\n\n        assertThat(adapter.toJson(BoxWithoutMoshi(\"unused\"))).isEqualTo(\"\\\"box-types-java.lang.String\\\"\")\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    fun lookupDefaultsConstructorFindsKotlinDefaultsConstructor(): Unit {\n        val constructor = Util.lookupDefaultsConstructor(KotlinDefaultTarget::class.java)\n\n        assertThat(constructor.parameterTypes.last().name).isEqualTo(\"